# Cognizant Digital Nurture 5.0 — Java FSE Portfolio

### Candidate Profiles
* **Batch:** 2027 Placement Cohort
* **Track Assigned:** Java Full Stack Engineering (Java FSE)
* **Upskilling Timeline:** 3-Week Comprehensive Implementation Track

---

## 📌 Project Overview
This repository contains a unified showcase of engineering competencies requested during the Cognizant Digital Nurture 5.0 upskilling journey. Over a rigorous three-week period, all milestone tasks spanning client-side presentation layers, relational databases, and core algorithmic program structures were implemented, tested locally, and compiled into this structured workspace.

The repository is organized directly around the recommended learning sequence tracks:
1. **Module 1 (Frontend UI & Logic):** Local Community Event Portal (HTML5, CSS3, Bootstrap 5, Vanilla JavaScript, and jQuery patches).
2. **Module 2 (Database Layer):** 25 ANSI SQL relational architecture queries.
3. **Module 3 (Core Backend Engine):** 41 Object-Oriented Java programmatic assignments.

---

## 📂 Repository Folder Structure

```text
Digital-Nurture-JavaFSE/
│
├── .gitignore                   # Prevents IDE caches, compiled binaries, and .class files
├── README.md                    # Project documentation & verification roadmap
│
├── Module-1_Frontend/           # Milestone 1: Client Application Layer
│   ├── index.html               # Semantic portal entry-point & modern authentication gate
│   ├── help.html                # Detached secondary documentation resource 
│   ├── css/
│   │   └── styles.css           # Grid controls, CSS3 columns, resets, and typography
│   └── js/
│       └── main.js              # State arrays, DOM validation, and mock AJAX streams
│
├── Module-2_Database/           # Milestone 2: Data Persistent Layer
│   └── queries.sql              # The 25 mandatory queries extracted from MySQL Workbench
│
└── Module-3_Java_Backend/       # Milestone 3: Algorithmic Core Logic Layer
      ├── HelloWorld.java
      ├── SimpleCalculator.java
      └── ...                    # Rest of the 41 programmatic core Java solution files
